5","1220":"1220","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","Wales":"Wales","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Madog","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French Canadian: variant of   Madore  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Madore","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Armand, Eusebe, Fernand, Lucien, Normand, Adhemar, Adrien, Donat, Elzear, Francois, Gaetan, Gilles.","French Canadian: from a French shortened form of the Spanish personal name <i>Amador</i>, from Latin <i>Amator</i> (from <i>amator</i> ‘lover’), a Christian saint's name. Compare   Mador  .","In some cases possibly also Breton (<b>Madoré</b>): nickname meaning literally ‘good help’, from Old Breton <i>mat</i> ‘good’ and <i>uuoret</i> ‘help’."]}]},{"name":"Tudor","type":"FIRST","meanings":["The Anglicised form of the Welsh Tewdwr, a name derived from Theodore."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Tudor Ap Madog was born in 1250, in Montgomeryshire, Wales, his father, Madoc Ap Samuel, was 30 and his mother, Efa Verch Maredudd Fychan, was 26. He married Nest Ferch Tudor about 1280, in Wales. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1250–":"1250–Surnud","1250–Male":"1250–Surnud","1265–Female":"1265–Surnud","1285–Male":"1285–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1225":"1225","abt 1280":"umbes 1280","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","Wales":"Wales","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1250–":"1250–Kuollut","1250–Male":"1250–Kuollut","1265–Female":"1265–Kuollut","1285–Male":"1285–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1225":"1225","abt 1280":"noin 1280","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","Wales":"Wales","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1250–":"1250–Décédé","1250–Male":"1250–Décédé","1265–Female":"1265–Décédée","1285–Male":"1285–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1225":"1225","abt 1280":"environ 1280","1265":"1265","1220":"1220","1285":"1285","1250":"1250","Wales":"Galles","Montgomery, Wales":"Montgomery, Montgomeryshire, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Tudor Ap Madog est né en 1250, à Montgomeryshire, Galles, son père, Madoc Ap Samuel, avait 30 ans et sa mère, Efa Verch Maredudd Fychan, avait 26 ans. Il a épousé Nest Ferch Tudor environ 1280, à Galles. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"1250–":"1250–Verstorben","1250–Male":"1250–Verstorben","1265–Female":"1265–Verstorben","1285–Male":"1285–Verstorben","1220–Male":"1220–Verstorben","1225–Female":"12